    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "Alternatively, there could be a symbolic arrays for any type of arrays and arrays would be accessed by indexing into these arrays. But depending on how often these kind of things happen, https://github.com/ethereum/solidity/issues/9148#issuecomment-640465177 might be more efficient and easier on the solvers.\r\n(Arrays of arrays would even have to be arrays of indices into the \"global\" array for the base type of the inner array for ``uint[] storage b = a[x];`` to work... not sure how indices would be assigned, s.t. exactly the right ones are distinct and the right ones are equal, etc...)",
